{"type":"message","id":"202c6dbd","parentId":"f3fbf825","timestamp":"2026-03-28T00:04:25.875Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the sessions_list results:\n\n1. `agent:main:cron:3709e1d2-67b1-4eff-92e4-b586ec802978` - This is the current cron job session itself. Its messages show it just started and only has the cron job's own message.\n\n2. `agent:main:cron:99dd3c6e-f440-4ce5-a3aa-579918ee141b` - This is another cron job (\"服务状态巡检\") that was aborted.\n\nNeither of these represents an active user conversation. These are both cron job sessions. The question is whether there are any user conversations in the last 5 minutes.\n\nThe sessions returned don't show any actual user messages - they show cron job sessions with \"systemSent\": true. This means these are system-triggered sessions, not user conversations.\n\nI don't see any actual user conversation sessions in the list. The only sessions are:\n1. The current cron job session (which is me processing)\n2. Another cron job session that was aborted\n\nSo there appear to be no active user conversations in the last 5 minutes. I should proceed with the self-learning task.\n\nLet me search for the latest trends in 企业数字化转型、智能安防、网络系统集成、IT运维服务.","thinkingSignature":"815d9073e5b8e9111c1618b76d95ebd12a462b8e14413c56157e197f64d50618"},{"type":"text","text":"检测到当前只有cron任务会话，没有用户活跃对话。执行自主学习。\n"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1175,"output":319,"cacheRead":43981,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45475,"cost":{"input":0.0003525,"output":0.0003828,"cacheRead":0.00131943,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00205473}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774656252168}}
